---
title: Sarh — Sign-in sequence (POST /api/v1/auth/sign-in)
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as Citizen / Officer
    participant Web as apps/web<br/>(Angular)
    participant Proxy as Dev proxy /<br/>nginx
    participant API as .NET 8 API<br/>AuthController
    participant DB as SQL Server<br/>(auth_users + officers)
    participant JWT as JwtTokenService<br/>(HS256)

    User->>Web: enters email + password
    Web->>Proxy: POST /api/v1/auth/sign-in<br/>{email, password}
    Proxy->>API: forwards (origin=:5000)

    API->>DB: SELECT auth_users WHERE email=?
    alt user not found
        DB-->>API: null
        API-->>Web: 401 ERR_UNAUTHORIZED
    else user found
        DB-->>API: user row
        Note over API: BCrypt.Verify(password, hash)
        alt wrong password
            API-->>Web: 401 ERR_UNAUTHORIZED
        else correct password
            API->>DB: SELECT officers WHERE auth_user_id=?
            DB-->>API: officer row or null
            Note over API: ResolveRoleAndCitizen()<br/>officer.role ?? raw_app_meta_data.sarh_role
            API->>JWT: SignAccessToken({sub, email,<br/>sarh_role, citizen_id, officer_id})
            JWT-->>API: { token, expires_in }
            API->>DB: UPDATE auth_users<br/>SET last_sign_in_at = NOW()
            API-->>Web: 200 { access_token, refresh_token,<br/>expires_in, user }
            Web->>Web: localStorage.setItem('sarh.access_token')
            Web->>Web: navigate to homeFor(role) → /app/dashboard
        end
    end
